---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Terms of Service - Usage Guidelines | QR Barcode Tools";
const description =
    "Read our terms of service. Our QR code and barcode generator tools are provided on an as-is basis for personal and commercial usage.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
        <div
            class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/80 p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm space-y-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm md:text-base"
        >
            <h1
                class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 border-b border-slate-100 pb-4"
            >
                Terms of Service
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Last updated: June 17, 2026</p>

            <p>
                By accessing and using <strong>QR Barcode Tools</strong>, you
                agree to comply with and be bound by the following terms and
                conditions. If you do not agree with any of these terms, please
                discontinue use of our tools.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                1. Permitted Usage & License
            </h2>
            <p>
                Our tools are provided entirely free of charge for both
                **personal and commercial purposes**. You may:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
                <li>Generate and download unlimited QR codes and barcodes.</li>
                <li>
                    Print downloaded barcode/QR graphics on retail packaging,
                    business signs, assets, or commercial materials.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Use our generated assets without paying royalties,
                    attribution fees, or watermarks.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                2. "As-Is" Disclaimer (Liability Limit)
            </h2>
            <p>
                Our tools and services are provided on an <strong
                    >"As-Is"</strong
                > and <strong>"As-Available"</strong> basis. While we verify our generation
                libraries against standard GS1 and ISO/IEC barcode protocols, we do
                not guarantee:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
                <li>
                    That the generated codes will scan successfully on all
                    legacy scanning devices.
                </li>
                <li>
                    That your custom colors will offer high enough contrast for
                    retail scanning.
                </li>
                <li>That our service will be uninterrupted or error-free.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We are not liable for any physical or digital financial damages
                (including inventory reprint costs, packaging waste, shipment
                quarantine, or logistics delays) resulting from the use or scan
                failure of our tools.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                3. Retail Number Registration Warning
            </h2>
            <p>
                You are solely responsible for ensuring that any EAN-13 or UPC-A
                numbers you input into our generators are legally leased and
                registered to your company via **GS1**. Using unauthorized,
                guessed, or stolen barcode numbers on retail products violates
                international logistics guidelines and may result in retail
                distribution bans and legal penalties.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                4. Modifications to Terms
            </h2>
            <p>
                We reserve the right to modify these terms of service at any
                time without prior announcement. It is your responsibility to
                review this page periodically to remain compliant with our
                current guidelines.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
